STATE: Delhi (Code: DL)
Enforcement Level: Very High
Notes: Delhi uses specific fixed fines, often higher than central. ANPR cameras active at 800+ junctions.

SPECIFIC FINE OVERRIDES IN DELHI:
  MV181: {"no_dl": 5000, "learner_alone": 5000}
  MV183: {"LMV_first": 2000, "HGV_first": 4000}
  MV184: {"signal_jump": 5000, "mobile_phone": 5000, "wrong_side": 5000}
  MV185: {"first": 10000, "subsequent": 15000}
  MV192: {"no_rc": 5000}
  MV194B: {"no_seatbelt": 1000}
  MV194D: {"no_helmet": 1000}
  MV196: {"no_insurance": 2000}

ADDITIONAL RULES IN DELHI:
  - Odd-even scheme applicable on weekdays 8AM-10AM and 5PM-9PM in winter
  - No-parking zones strictly enforced with towing
  - BS-VI vehicles mandatory for new registrations

